docs.abstract: People and companies with vested interest in sustaining the U.S.-China relationship are stepping in as ties fray between the two countries.
docs.snippet: People and companies with vested interest in sustaining the U.S.-China relationship are stepping in as ties fray between the two countries.
docs.lead_paragraph: HONG KONG — U.S. hospitals and state officials face desperate shortages of the masks, ventilators and other gear they need to fight the coronavirus. Chinese factories can make the equipment and sell it to them, but huge obstacles stand in the way — and Washington’s stumbles and growing hostility with Beijing aren’t helping.
